Business Online Banking


Giving You Control from Your Office or Home.
Business online banking at Howard Bank is an important service. It provides you with instant and confidential access to your business accounts. If you are interested in business online banking, let your Relationship Manager know. We’ll meet with you so that we can set up the account exactly as you’d like it to be.

By utilizing Howard Bank’s Business Online Banking Service, Treasury Information Reporting service, you will have access to view the balances online to include the information described below.  You can view, print, and download intra-day and previous business day account information for your accounts at Howard Bank.  This application supports download of reports, as needed, into your accounting, treasury workstation, or spreadsheet applications.  Download and viewing options include BAI, Comma Separated Variable (CSV), Excel, HTML, and PDF.
In addition, your business can search for specific transactions by account number, account type, currency, date or date range, debit or credit transaction type, amount or amount range, reference number or reference number range and location number or location number range.  You can view details for each transaction, whether paper or electronic.  The reporting system allows you to quickly search for posted items, initiate stop payments, renew or release stops and view online images of checks, electronic deposits or paper deposits that have posted to your accounts.  Designed as a one-stop shop for access to banking services, this web-based platform will allow you to do the following:

Review Previous Day Account Activity.
Determine Current Day Account Balance.
Retrieve Images of Paid Checks.
Retrieve Copies of Monthly Bank Statements.
Initiate Stop Payments.
Initiate Internal Transfers between Howard Bank Accounts.
Initiate ACH Files through the Funds Management Module.
Initiate Wire Transfers through the Funds Management Module.
Initiate Bill Payments through the Funds Management Module.

 
Enrollment
We handle our enrollments by phone. To discuss enrollment or get further information, please contact our Business Online Banking Department at 410-750-0020. Thank you for your interest in Business Online Banking, our online cash management service.




